# Posit — Windsurf Rules

All project rules, architecture, and conventions live in `CLAUDE.md`.
**Read `CLAUDE.md` first, every session.** This file exists only to point
Windsurf at the shared instructions.

## Harness Sync
Slash commands exist in both `.claude/commands/` (Claude Code, primary) and
`.windsurf/workflows/` (Windsurf, secondary). Their bodies must match
byte-for-byte. When editing any command, update **both** files in the same
commit. A Stop hook in `.claude/settings.json` warns on drift.

## Windsurf-Specific
- **Auto-plan mode:** enter Plan Mode on every non-trivial task. Output a
  step-by-step plan and pause for explicit approval before editing files.
- **Surgical commits:** list exact paths via `git add path1 path2`, never
  `git add .` or `git add -A`.
- **State awareness:** if a file you are editing changes unexpectedly
  mid-edit, another agent may have touched it. Stop and ask for conflict
  resolution.
